Vice President Kamala Harris held a discussion with tribal leaders to address voting rights issues, particularly those affecting Native American communities. She emphasized the importance of recognizing the historical barriers faced by Native Americans in exercising their right to vote and highlighted the ongoing challenges, such as lack of access to polling locations and language barriers. Harris called for the passage of the For the People Act and the John Lewis Voting Rights Act to protect voting rights for all Americans. Secretary of the Interior Deb Haaland also spoke about the significance of protecting the right to vote in federal elections across Indian Country and shared her personal experience of registering voters in tribal communities. The Vice President urged people to get vaccinated against COVID-19, emphasizing the importance of vaccination in preventing serious illness and death from the virus.